<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-909-623  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 909 623.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  Sept 11 1989 v11 n37 p5(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>PM outline font agreement in the works. (Presentation Manager)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Flynn, Laurie.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Microsoft and IBM hope to agree on how they will implement fontsin OS/2 Presentation Manager (PM).andP;  Both firms will probably adoptthe Intelligent Font Interface (IFI), an IBM-favored architecturethat will let vendors and users include their own preferredfont-scaling software.andP;  Under IFI, users would be able to mixlibraries in a single document and font vendors would supply theirfont-scaling software as dynamic link libraries.andP;  IFI's primedrawback is that users would still have to correct fonts when theycommunicate with a printer or microcomputer.andP;  Microsoft favors acommon font technology for screen images and printers.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   International Business Machines Corp. (product development)Microsoft Corp. (product development).andO;Product:   OS/2 Presentation Manager (Graphical user interface) (computerprograms).andO;Topic:     FontsCooperative AgreementStandardizationProduct Development.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>